Pre-Game Insights: Each side topped their regional qualifiers with six wins from six. The top of Group B is now at stake
David Wiese and Ruben Trumpelmann are key performers for Namibia
George Munsey and Michael Jones dispatched England's bowlers for 90 runs in ten overs either side of a two-hour rain delay
Miscellaneous Highlights: The magic number would appear to be 109, to judge by the two very contrasting clashes that have so far taken place in Group B of the T20 World Cup 2024
And so it's back to Bridgetown we go for two teams that have been on a significant roll since the end of their respective campaigns at the last T20 World Cup in 2022
Others: Scotland will be confident after impressing against England

If Scotland can grab the extra point that eluded them last time out, then maintain their 100% record in T20Is against Oman when they meet in Antigua in Sunday, then they will go into their final group game against Australia next week with qualification in their own hands

Irrespective of whether Tuesday's washout was an opportunity won or lost for Scotland, the fact that Group B's top seeds fell short of their anticipated two points means the door is ajar for a notable upset, particularly if Australia can inflict further damage on England's standing in Saturday's heavyweight clash
